               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Daily Office Prayers and Litanies (fols. 2ra l.1–13ra l.21)
 II)
                     Śǝrʿāta qǝddāse “Ordinary of the Mass” (fols. 13rb l.1–26vb l.2)
 III)
                     Anaphoras (fol. 26vb–112vb)
 III-1) Anaphora of the Apostles (fols. 26vb
                     l.3–32va l.13)
 III-2) Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols. 32va
                     l.14–36ra l.9)
 III-3) Anaphora of Our Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa
                     (fols. 36ra l.10–46vb l.18)
 III-4) Anaphora of St Dioscorus (fols. 46vb
                     l.18–49vb l.11)
 III-5) Anaphora of St John Chrysostom (fols. 49vb
                     l.12–55ra l.15)
 III-6) Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox Fathers of Nicaea
                     (fols. 55ra l.16–63rb l.16)
 III-7) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols.
                     63rb l.16–70vb l.12)
 III-8) Anaphora of St Athanasius (fols. 70vb
                     l.12–81vb l.18)
 III-9) Anaphora of St Gregory (fols. 82ra l.1–87vb
                     l.5)
 III-10) Anaphora of St John, son of Thunder (fols. 87vb l.6–97rb
                     l.16)
 III-11) Anaphora of St Epiphanius (fols. 97rb l.17–103vb l.13)
                     III-12) Anaphora of St Basil of Caesarea (fols. 103vb l.15–112vb l.7)
 IV)
                     Regulations concerning prerequisites for participation in the Eucharistic
                     Liturgy (fols. 112vb l.8–113rb l.7)
 
 Additiones 1-3.</summary>
