                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1va">f. 1va</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#1va">1va</locus>: ዝቅዳሴ፡ ዘቂርቆስ፡ ሃራ፡ ዘተሰየጦ፡ ወልደ፡ ሥላሴ፡
                              ከሙት፡ ኵነኒ፡ መድኀኒተ፡ ነፍሴ፡ ኢትሕድጉኒ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ለዘላለም፡ ሥላሴ። ዘሰረቃ፡ ወዘፈሐቃ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡
                              ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#1va">1va</locus>:  This missal of Qirqos Hara was
                              purchased by Walda Śǝllāse (so that it might be) salvation for my soul
                              from condemnation to death. Don’t abandon me the Trinity forever the
                              Trinity. May be condemned forever whoever steals it and erases
                              it.</quote>
                           <note> </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#1va">f. 1va</locus>
                           <desc>-vb: Donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#1va">1va-</locus>b: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘወልደ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ለቅዱስ፡
                              ቂርቆስ፡ ወዘአጽሐፎ፡ አቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖሙ፡ መርሃ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት። ወአቡሁ፡ ወልደ፡
                              ሳሙኤል፡ ገብረ፡ ዋህድ፡ ዘርዓ፡ ጽዮን፡ ወእሙ፡ ወለተ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ወለተ፡ ጽዮን፡ እምነ፡ ጽዮን፡ ወለተ፡
                              ኤልሳቤጥ፡ አመተ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ዘተጽሕፈት፡ በዘመነ፡ ንጉሥነ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ወጳጳስነ፡ አትናቴዎስ፡ ወቄስ፡ ገበዝ፡
                              ወልደ፡ ኪሮስ፡ ወባሕር፡ ነጋሲ፡ ተወልደ ፡ መድኅን፡ ወእኁሁ፡ ወልደ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወአቡሆሙ፡ ገብረ፡ አደንያስ፡
                              ወጸሐፊሃ፡ አቡነ፡ ወልደ፡ ሙሴ።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#1va">1va-</locus>b: Let this book of Walda Śǝllāse
                              which he donated to the Saint Qirqos [Church] and which commissioned
                              ʾabuna Gabra Māryām become a guide to the Kingdom of Heaven. And (for)
                              his father Walda Sāmuʾel Gabra Wahǝd Zärʿa Ṣǝyon and his mother
                              Walatta Giyorgis, Walatta Ṣǝyon, ʾƎmmǝnä Ṣǝyon, Walatta ʾElsabeṭ,
                              ʾAmata Mikāʾel. It was written in the time of our king Yoḥannǝs and
                              our metropolitan ʾAtnatewos and qesa gabaz Walda Kiros and baḥr nagāśi
                              Tawalda Madḫǝn and his brother Walda Krǝstos and their father Gabra
                              Adänyas and the scribe (is) Walda Muse.</quote>
                           <note> </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#113rb">f. 113rb</locus>
                           <desc>ls.9-21: Donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#113rb">113rb</locus> ls.9-21: ዝቅዳሴ፡ ዘቂርቆስ፡ ሃራ፡ ዘወሀቦ፡
                              ወልደ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ወዘአጽሐፍዋ፡ አቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡ ወጸሐፊሃ፡ አቡነ፡ ወልደ፡ ሙሴ፡ ዋጋ ፱ ብር፡ ነው… </quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#113rb">113rb</locus> ls.9-21: This missal of Qirqos
                              Hara which donated Walda Śǝllāse and which commissioned ʾabuna Gabra
                              Māryām and wrote ʾabuna Walda Muse costs 9 bǝrr...</quote>
                           <note> The information about the price is in Amharic (9 Bǝrr). The note
                              indicates the names of the donor, the scribe, the commissioner (the
                              same as in Additio 1 and 2) and the price for which the Ms. was
                              purchased by the donor. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Notes in the upper margin: <locus target="#35r">35r</locus>, 36r, 90v.
 - Notes in pen, within the main text
                           field: <locus target="#101v">101v</locus>, 102r.
 - Minor note (pen
                           trial?): <locus target="#113v">113v</locus>.
 - Short text; words are
                           written without spaces or punctuation signs between them; its meaning is
                           unclear, possibly an exercise in writing (cp. the initial words:
                           ብርዕዘፈቲነ…): <locus target="#114r">114r</locus>.
 - Pen trials: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, 1v.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
